mp;_nc_gid=uITLt7fUNQqptdJ3DG1jyA&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfyDYGA9_BuioVq72elyd8YKq0DU70tS4kvdPmYhewvaSg&amp;oe=69CA40BC" alt="Slide 3 fra @richipetrini" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/645777361_18571500679015331_543144896860253521_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg0Mzg1NzQyMDcwNzk3Nzc5NQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjcyMHg5NTguc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=jhaQM79IYBcQ7kNvwEcwrrf&amp;_nc_oc=AdrvZ2Om472GCg6YZWiYInHghd0JzImWexUMv_0ddF-_HJaBKZenJZpqUafXOrvrpcw&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=uITLt7fUNQqptdJ3DG1jyA&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afzm2-yq5mPRIVfcbhBG8bihUAppPMacpZLoHM-NeCMUCQ&amp;oe=69CA38AE" alt="Slide 4 fra @richipetrini" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /></p><p><strong>🖼️ Slideshow (6 medier)</strong></p><p><strong>@richipetrini</strong></p><p>● On the “craft” within the FinneGAN interface<br/>
FinneGAN is a GAN model trained on Finnegans Wake. When you enter the interface, the model is initialized and begins generating new sentences from a binary latent code. Each initialization produces a unique output. Rather than presenting only the output, the interface allows you to traverse the intermediate representations of the network—from early, noisy activations to the final pre-linguistic signal. The organization of these levels of articulation is analogous to an ascent and descent through the clouds. The interface comprises vertical travel through a stack of volumetric clouds, each corresponding to a specific internal convolutional layer of the GAN.<br/>
The stack is organized by density: in the lower, denser clouds, the generation remains fuzzy and dominated by noise. As you move upward, the cloud density decreases and the output becomes progressively more articulated.<br/>
Slides:<br/>
1. The navigation logic through the internal convolutional layers of the finneGAN model, driven by the cursor’s position over time.<br/>
2. The transcription space records the history of internal navigation and includes:<br/>
– the binary latent code fed to the finneGAN<br/>
– the currently active convolutional layer<br/>
– the directionality of navigation<br/>
– the transcription generated using OpenAI’s Whisper Tiny speech-to-text model<br/>
3. Detail view showing the fragment shader computing over time, producing emergent behavior in response to the cursor movement.<br/>
4. Abstract diagram of an ascent through cloud layers corresponding to increasingly discrete articulations.<br/>
5. The fully assembled finneGAN interface. <br/>
6. Example .json response. To enable working directly from within the model, the internal convolutional layers are exposed as discrete API endpoints that can be queried independently.</p><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DVYIHSMjC86/">Se slideshow på Instagram</a></p>]]></description>
